<br>
I know a lot of bards on here do a lot of pulling in hard LDoN adventures and was wondering if you could give me a few pointers.  The last couple adventures i've been on have gone all right, but i'd really like to fine tune my pulling style to be able to work well in a hard adventure.<br>
<br>
I've tried mez pulling in these adventures and found that if a debuff doesn't take place beforehand that mez rarely ever lands on the first shot.<br>
<br>
That got me thinking about a post i saw earlier here about bards in PoFire mezzing mobs.  Talk turned to a bards level of Jamfest and a bards ability to mez mobs there.  Does this hold true in hard adventures too?  I have Jamfest 2 right now and am working towards Jamfest 3... will that make some difference in mez pulling?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for your help, <p><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168467" target="_new">Impressario Khar Wraithdirge</a><br>
Maestro of Shar Vahl<br>
Heretics of the Apocalypse</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub147.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kimonawindfall>Kimona Windfall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#330000>(1/22/04 11:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallontour.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=307.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~larry1015/_uimages/new.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LDoN Hard pulling Question</span><hr size=1> I’ve found that I don’t have too many problems pulling high risk LDoNs with just JF1 so you should be more than ok with JF2. I can mez just fine and I have very few critical fails with lull. Lull gets resisted quite a bit, sure, but rarely do I aggro. And if I do aggro on lull, I’ll mez one and drag 2 to camp if it’s 3 mobs or less. More mobs than that, I just FM them off and try again. Plus I always make sure I grab a Charisma buff before I head on in. It may or may not help with lull but I’m kinda superstitious and I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>feel</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> like it does. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Once you get that going for you, you’ll find that regular pulling methods work fine. Just make sure that you have plenty of pulling space. Biggest tip, if you blow a pull, don't drag the mobs to the group. Don't be afraid to take one for the team. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Don’t let yourself be intimidated by high risk adventures. As long as you have a solid group, you’ll be fine. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=16089" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~larry1015/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/kyrana3.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub147.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=saevroksirensong>Saevrok Sirensong</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#330000>(1/22/04 2:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallontour.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=307.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LDoN Hard pulling Question</span><hr size=1> Twist in Charisma when lulling, it will save you a headache when they resist, use solidarity of vision to sight jump and harmo, and remember, it isnt a matter of getting every mob single, its a matter of getting as few as you can. <p>Saevrok 65th Bard <br>
