<br>
I lull what I can around and I go for single or double pulls as much as possible, but ALWAYS leave 1 free room between my group and my pulls, this way if I run into trouble I have room to split.<br>
<br>
Make sure your tank understands how you work, my tanks all know that when I pull if I pull multiples I will let them know with each hit of the incoming key how many are coming(standard for any puller I know), they also know that I'm going to mez my target first of all, so if I say incoming spider, and here comes a spider and a ghost, well they know to attack the ghost.<br>
<br>
I do a lot of mezzing mobs in my empty room, this gives me more control over things.<br>
<br>
Depending on how much mana you have for fades and what your FT is will also determine your pull style, I can fade about 7 times in a row if need be and I have max FT, but I rarely use FM anymore because I have a pretty solid understanding now after over 100 hard missions on how things work.<br>
<br>
Practice makes perfect, the more experience you get pulling, the better you will be at it. Good luck <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">RETIRED 3-20-2003</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=259301" target="top"><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.shaw.ca/dragonas/sig/gnalp.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub147.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=huricrazyshorty>Huri Crazyshorty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#330000>(2/1/04 9:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallontour.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=307.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LDoN Hard pulling Question</span><hr size=1> Mez, Lull and Snare are your big toys.<br>
<br>
I like using Largos - if Mez isn't landing, at least they are somewhat slower <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The idea of a room as a buffer zone is the real key.<br>
<br>
I think it's safe to say that if you are at the point of pulling a &quot;hard&quot;, you can geenrally tank an &quot;easy&quot; .<br>
<br>
Maps are key, too. watch out for the blind corners, and the stupid aggro areas.<br>
<br>
Build up your confidence in Rujarkian hills doing hards. They have the most space, and you will learn your own methods best there.<br>
<br>
Tak can have maps where chain aggro in rooms is uhmm...pleasant.<br>
<br>
