<br>
For single pulls just.. well.. pull them<br>
For double pulls, mez one of the mobs and bring the other one to the group, letting mez (or if you have an enchanter, let him overwrite your mez so you can twist better) land on the one in the room. If you have a decent DPS group, you can stop mezzing it at about 15-20% hp and the mez will fade and it will come a couple seconds after the first mob is dead.<br>
<br>
For triple pulls, start singing mez on one mob, quickly change target to another one that will come, and right after mez hits on that one start singing mez on the other one as your running back to your group. What I usually do then is to FM off the first one I mezzed and continue mezzing the second one (which means that the next two will be singles)<br>
<br>
For quad pulls ( =( ) start to sing the mez on a mob in the room, switch targets like you did for the triple pull, mez the second, then (at about the same time you get back to your group) you start mezzing the third one. FM off the two you mezzed earlier (If mez is already on them, you don't get agro when mez breaks)<br>
<br>
For five pulls.. well.. I haven't seen a five in one pull room yet<br>
<br>
